Grasping the OSI Model

Packet analysis requires a solid understanding of encapsulation and protocols

Standardizes the functions of data transformations
Breaks down into layers
Outlines how data is encapsulated



Key Points


PDU - Protocol Data Unit

7.Applications Layer - Initiates contact with the network  (Protocols - HTTP,FTP,SMTP)  (PDU - Data)

6.Presentation Layer - Formats data, optional compression, and encryption (PDU - Data)

5.Session Layer - Initiates, maintains and tears down session (PDU - Data)

4.Transport Layer - Transports data (Protocols - TCP,UDP)   (PDU - Segment)  Address - Port

3.Network Layer - Addressing,routing (Protocols - IP,ICMP)  (PDU - Packet)  Address - IP

2.Data Link Layer - Frame formation (Protocols - Ethernet II)  (PDU - Frame) Address - MAC

1.Physical Layer - Data is transmitted on the media  (PDU - Bits)


